$ Python: exec

code {
statement_1  = 'num = 42'
statement_2  = 'print(num)'
statements   = '''
num = num * 2
print(num)
'''

exec(statement_1)
exec(statement_2)
exec(statements )
code }


sa:
 ? `exec` is applied to a *statement* while → development/languages/Python/built-in-functions/eval[`eval`] is applied to an *expression*.

  → development/languages/Python/built-in-functions
